Tracker Vision Volume 2 is coming along great. I’ve finished 3 tracks for what will be a 7 track album and couldnt be happier with how these are turning out. Ive decided to start posting clips of each song so you guys have a chance to see what i’ve been up to! This album will make use of the N163 expansion chip that Namco designed for the original Nintendo! This chip allowed composers to use up to 8 extra channels of Wave Table synthesis to enhance their compositions! It has been such a joy to work with this synth! This song here is called “Wave Dancer” and is the first track on the album!!! The gameplay footage is from a shmup called “Fantasy Zone” for the NES!!!! More clips coming soon!!!!!
.
.
.

Happy Holidays everyone. 2022 was an amazing year for me. I won my first grammy with @crosenmusic and @the8bitbigband . I released a single with @wearephoenix and several more with @videogamedj as well as two of my own full length  albums. I sold out my first headliner in Seattle thanks to @goodbyelookclub and @pmanfitness .Times were still tough for me this year but i got a lot of signs from the universe that i’m doing what i was put on this earth to do. I am extremely grateful to everyone who has streamed my music, purchased my albums and shown up to my live shows. Thank you all and much love to you. Looking forward to 2023. Things are looking bright.
.

My brilliant brother @israelstrommusic made this AWESOME polyrhythm warmup and i couldnt help but take a swing at it myself. For mine i decided to use a short chord progression in Cminor and used Super Midi Pak to make it into a super nintendo tune. This exercise is really great and i cant reccomend it enough. The sequence is: 6:4 3:4 8:4 4:4 10:4 5:4 12:4 6:4. Give it a try sometime!

“Everywhere You Look” from “Full House” in the style of “Earthbound” for Super Nintendo. This will be my last post of the year. Thank you all for an absolutely amazing year. I look back on this year with enormous pride at what i managed to accomplish. If I learned anything this year, its that i was put on this earth to make chiptune and to be a voice in the effort to preserve this great art form that has been a part of many of our lives in one way or another. So much music and so many new things coming next year. Thank you all a million times over.

Possible future project “Chiptune for Lovers”: A Button Masher Jazz Standards album. Good idea? Bad Idea? Anyway, heres “Ive Never Been In Love Before” in the style of the Game Over music from Super Mario world using Super Midi Pak. I havent done solo piano in a long time. Partially because i know so many great pianists that i feel like i cant live up to the standard that i see so regularly set by my peers. My resolution this year is to overcome that anxiety and do more things like this. I hope you guys enjoy it.
.

“Evidence” by Thelonious Monk reimagined on the Nintendo Entertainment System. For this arrangement i used the default 2A03 soundchip and the N163 expansion audio. This track will be featured on my next album and is particularly special as it features my good friend @henryrsolomon on tenor sax! To stay true to the hardware limitations of the NES, my friend damifortune downsampled the sax solo and cut it up into tiny segments that we reassembled in famitracker. Im super proud of this piece. More preview clips coming soon.

Recently I’ve been obsessed with trying to authentically recreate various musical styles with Super Midi Pak. This past week i took a swing at writing a break beat for it. Break Beats tend to be highly active on drums. This presented an interesting challenge as the super nintendo can only play 8 notes at any given time. To accommodate this limitation, i made the drum track almost entirely monophonic but extremely active so as to create the illusion that many drums are being played at once. I used samples from Final Fantasy 4, Kirby Super Star, Terranigma, and Secret of mana. The midi file, project file, and wav file for this song and many others are available for download on my patreon! Link in my link tree! ALSO PLEASE COME TO MY SHOW IN NYC 7/19/23!!!!!! TICKET LINK IN BIO!!!!!! September show tickets with @skatunenetwork are selling fast so get those too! All in the link tree!!!!

Jazz and 16-bit worlds collide in “Super Standards!” 
Performed and arranged by Button Masher, “Super Standards” is a concept album that reimagines 12 jazz standards in the styles of Super Nintendo games.

Button Masher is Jake Silverman, a Grammy award-winning arranger and pianist. He is also known for his viral 16-bit and chiptune covers and collaborations with Dj Cutman and The 8-Bit Big Band. With his roots in jazz and live performance, and a passion for videogame music, Jake bridges both worlds in “Super Standard”.

“Super Standards” features 12 jazz favorites, each in the unique styles of some of the greatest games for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System. The tracklisting includes universal favorites such as “Somewhere Over the Rainbow”, “My Favorite Things”, and “Just The Way You Are”, and tracks “Poinciana” and “Humpty Dumpty” pay tribute to the legacy of late jazz musicians Ahmad Jamal and Chick Corea respectively. Using real SNES hardware and a device called the Super MIDI Pak, Button Masher interprets these classics as melodies from Super Mario World, Donkey Kong Country, A Link to the Past, Kirby Super Star, Yoshi’s Island, Pilotwings, and RPGs Chrono Trigger, Secret of Mana, and Earthbound. “Super Standards” features compositions by Wayne Shorter, Antonio Carlos Jobim, Nat Simon, Chick Corea, and more.

“Super Standards” is out now on all online stores and streaming platforms! Support Button Masher and GameChops by streaming, saving, and adding the tracks to your playlists.

I am extremely excited to announce that my album with @gamechops is out on all streaming platforms NOW! This album bridges together my roots in jazz with my passion for Super Nintendo music. All 12 jazz standards on this album are arranged in the style of some of the most Iconic titles in gaming history. Here is a preview of what you have to look forward to. At 12 noon EST today, there will be an entire video concert of all 12 selections from the album on the Gamechops youtube channel! Would love to see you there! Stream “Super Standards” TODAY!

I am elated to share that the reception to “Super Standards has been overwhelming. I would like to share a reel showcasing one of my favorite selections on the album. This year, we lost one of the greatest musical minds of all time. Im speaking of course, of the great Wayne Shorter. Wayne was not only one of the greatest Tenor Saxophonists of all time, he was also an incredibly influential composer and orchestrator. When thinking of how I could pay tribute to his work on this album, I immediately could imagine his ballad “Infant Eyes” reworked in the style of Yasunori Mitsudas “Secret of the Forest” from Chrono Trigger. Needless to say, these two works were a match made in heaven. Thank you for everything Wayne. Rest in Power.
.

In memory of one of my biggest personal heroes of the piano, i present my arrangement of “Humpty Dumpty” by Chick Corea in the style of “Kirby’s Dream Course”. One of my first Chick Corea albums was “Light as a feather” with Return to Forever. This abum lead me down a Chick Corea rabit hole from highschool onward. Humpty Dumpty has always been one of my favorite Chick tunes. I was immediately able to imagine how Hirokazu Ando’s style on Dream Course could work with this tune and the results speak for themselves. What is your favorite song on “Super Standards”?
.

Back in the day when the only music you could listen to was either on the radio or what ever CD’s you had around the house, my parents had several Billy Joel cds that I absolutely loved as a child. So many of his songs bring about such powerful feelings of nostalgia for me. I get the same feeling when I play games like “Super Mario World 2: Yoshi’s Island”. It made so much sense to put “Just The Way You Are” with the sounds from Yoshi’s Island and Im very glad to have included this on “Super Standards”. Hope you guys enjoy!

This time however, we had the distinct honor of being joined by the one and only Jonah Nilson from @dirtyloopsofficial on our arrangement of “The Last Surprise” from Persona 5! I am so proud to announce that my first “How To Chiptune” Tutorial video is now LIVE on youtube!!!! For those of you who have wondered how i make authentic music for retro gaming consoles, the wait is over! The first video covers a very important topic: How to Learn Chiptune trackers. Many people have come to me saying that they want to learn how to use trackers but they feel that its just too much of a lift. This video will tell you everything you need to know and will provide a learning strategy that will have you tracking confidently in less than a month!!!! Going forward i will be covering topics like “How to make Snes Music in 2023” and “how to write music in the style of your favorite video game composers”. Subscribe to my youtube channel today to never miss a tutorial!!!!!!

The remix that my version is based on is “A Pimp Named Slick Back” by Lakim. For the nerds out there: yes everything your hearing was written and recorded on a super nintendo including the vocal samples. Would love to see some people dance to this one.

Its a full length reimagining of the song in the style of Super Mario World! This track is now on all streaming platforms for you to enjoy. The footage you are seeing is of the legendary @ryukahr speed running what looks to be a fairly challenging super mario world rom hack! I was in the Grocery store the other day when “Forget Me Nots” by Patrice Rushen started playing over the speaker system. Such an amazing song. I decided i had to cover it and after going through all of my favorite super Nintendo soundtracks to draw sounds from, i settled on one of my all time favorites “Secret of Mana”. Anyone who knows me knows this game is one of my all time favorites and the soundtrack by Hiroki Kikuta is one of the most Iconic OSTs on the snes. Might release a full version later this year. Quick reminder that I have 2 shows coming up. 2/7/24 Nublu NYC 2/17/24 Bad Bar Seattle! Ticket links in the bio!
